                            <comment id="13727474" author="njiang" created="Fri, 2 Aug 2013 08:13:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you submit a simple test case for us to dig the issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13728303" author="avina" created="Sat, 3 Aug 2013 00:13:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;a test case&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13729058" author="avina" created="Mon, 5 Aug 2013 01:11:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;About the test case:&lt;br/&gt;
I compared PAYLOAD with POJO. Both tests failed when the &quot;synchronous&quot; property set to &quot;false&quot;. That&apos;s another problem I found. &lt;br/&gt;
With &quot;synchronous=true&quot;, POJO test passed but PAYLOAD test stuck.&lt;br/&gt;
A ClassCastException was thrown at line 869 in CxfEndpoint.java .&lt;br/&gt;
Detail:&lt;br/&gt;
 javax.xml.transform.dom.DOMSource cannot be cast to org.apache.camel.component.cxf.CxfPayload&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13729487" author="njiang" created="Mon, 5 Aug 2013 12:56:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just fixed the ClassCastException, but it may take me some time to fix the synchronous issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
